Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @aubergine{1}, then cut into roughly 3cm pieces.

Pop the aubergine onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and half the @North Indian style spice mix{1/2}. Toss to coat, then arrange in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden brown and soft, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #medium saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the shallot and cook, stirring frequently, until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

While the shallot cooks, pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into another medium saucepan with a #tight-fitting lid{}. Stir in the @basmati rice{150} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Add the @korma curry paste{50}, fried paneer, garlic and remaining @North Indian style spice mix{1/2} to the shallot and cook, stirring frequently, for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1}, @red split lentils{100}, @vegetable stock paste{10}, @sugar{1} and @water for the dal{350%ml}. Combine and bring to a boil.

Lower the heat to medium and cook until the lentils are soft, ~{20-25%minutes}. Stir regularly to make sure they don't stick to the bottom of the pan and add a splash of water if it gets too thick.

Once the lentils are cooked, stir in the @baby spinach{40} a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir through the roasted aubergine and @paneer{226}(fried) and cook until everything's piping hot.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash more water if it's a little thick.

When everything's ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and spoon into your bowls.

Top with the aubergine and paneer dal and tuck in. Enjoy!